    {
      "title": "Form VIII Verbs (اِفْتَعَلَ)",
      "titleArabic": "الفعل في الباب الثامن",
      "content": [
        "Form VIII verbs follow the pattern اِفْتَعَلَ - يَفْتَعِلُ. This form typically indicates reflexive action, mutual action, or effort/struggle in doing something.",
        "The distinguishing feature is the infixed ت (ta) after the first radical."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Past pattern: اِفْتَعَلَ (e.g., اِجْتَمَعَ)",
        "Present pattern: يَفْتَعِلُ (e.g., يَجْتَمِعُ)",
        "Meanings: Reflexive, mutual, effort, or acquiring",
        "جَمَعَ (he gathered) → اِجْتَمَعَ (they gathered together)",
        "سَمِعَ (he heard) → اِسْتَمَعَ (he listened attentively)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اِجْتَمَعَ الطُّلَّابُ", "english": "The students gathered" },
        { "arabic": "اِسْتَمَعَ إِلَى الْمُعَلِّمِ", "english": "He listened to the teacher" },
        { "arabic": "اِخْتَارَ الْكِتَابَ", "english": "He chose the book" },
        { "arabic": "اِسْتَعَدَّ لِلاِمْتِحَانِ", "english": "He prepared for the exam" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Common Form VIII Verbs",
      "titleArabic": "أفعال شائعة من الباب الثامن",
